					<description><![CDATA[<p>Series A Funding Accelerates AI Healthcare Expansion Flok Health Raises $12.5M marks a major step for AI driven healthcare delivery. The Cambridge based company builds autonomous physiotherapy systems for musculoskeletal</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/flok-health-raises-12-5m-ai-healthcare/" data-wpel-link="internal">Flok Health Raises $12.5M to Scale AI Operated Healthcare Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Series A Funding Accelerates AI Healthcare Expansion</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok Health Raises $12.5M marks a major step for AI driven healthcare delivery. The Cambridge based company builds autonomous physiotherapy systems for musculoskeletal care. The Series A round was oversubscribed and led by Albion VC. Existing investors Eka Ventures and Form Ventures also participated. Mercia Ventures joined as a new investor in the round.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok Health Raises $12.5M brings total backing to support rapid clinical expansion. The funding will scale its AI operated clinic across the United Kingdom. It will also support expansion beyond back pain treatment pathways. The company is preparing an international rollout across new healthcare markets. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investor confidence reflects growing demand for scalable digital care systems. Founded in 2022, Flok Health was created by Finn Stevenson and Ric da Silva. Stevenson is a former medic and professional rower. Da Silva is a technologist with experience in surgical robotics systems. Together they aimed to solve structural gaps in healthcare delivery capacity.</span></p>
<h2><b>AI Operated Clinic Transforms Musculoskeletal Care Delivery</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok Health Raises $12.5M supports an AI clinic designed for full treatment delivery. The platform provides diagnosis, treatment plans, and rehabilitation guidance. It also delivers discharge decisions without clinician involvement. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Patients access care through a mobile application interface. The system uses real physiotherapist footage to simulate live consultations. Patients interact with a responsive AI driven clinical experience. The platform processes speech, movement, and patient input in real time. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It replicates human consultation flow while automating clinical reasoning. Flok is approved by the UK Care Quality Commission as a provider. It also holds Class IIa medical device certification for autonomous care. This makes it one of Europe’s most regulated AI healthcare systems. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It can triage, treat, and discharge patients independently. The service is already deployed across more than 2.4 million NHS patients. It operates across eleven UK regions. The platform has reduced waiting lists in several NHS deployments. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">It has also saved hundreds of clinical hours each month. In one rollout, over eighty percent of patients rated the service highly. They reported outcomes equal or better than in person physiotherapy. Clinical teams were freed to handle more complex cases.</span></p>
<h2><b>Scaling NHS Adoption and Expanding Care Pathways<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202342" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202342" class="size-full wp-image-202342" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-with_7ezlupn4UeWbTCiM2MW4Sg_iC8WXHvuQtqX_eY8BaFH2A_cover.png" alt="AI physiotherapy platform expanding into multiple treatment areas while reducing NHS patient backlog through automated care delivery. " width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202342" class="wp-caption-text">Flok Health expands AI-driven care beyond back pain to reduce NHS waiting list pressures and improve treatment access. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok Health Raises $12.5M will accelerate expansion into new treatment areas. The company plans to expand beyond musculoskeletal back pain care. New pathways include hip pain, knee pain, and pelvic health conditions. These areas represent high demand within healthcare systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The NHS continues to face significant waiting list pressures. More than 390,000 patients are currently awaiting MSK treatment in England. Back pain remains a leading cause of global disability. It also drives millions of lost workdays annually in the UK.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok’s AI system is designed to reduce this backlog. It delivers immediate treatment access without waiting lists. It also improves efficiency by reducing clinician workload. This allows specialists to focus on complex patient cases.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes AI can close structural gaps in healthcare supply. Demand for treatment continues to </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/outpace" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">outpace</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> clinician availability globally. Flok positions itself as a scalable solution to this imbalance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/oqc-raises-260m-quantum-computing-series-c/" data-wpel-link="internal">Oxford Quantum Circuit Raises £260M Led by Bullhound Capital</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Competitive AI Healthcare Landscape Intensifies Globally</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok Health Raises $12.5M places the company in a growing AI healthcare sector. Competitors include Sword Health and Hinge Health in the United States. These firms combine AI tools with human clinical oversight systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Sword Health raised $130 million at a $3 billion valuation recently. It uses AI guided therapy combined with motion tracking and sensors. Hinge Health operates a large digital therapy platform for enterprises. It raised $400 million at a $6.2 billion valuation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok takes a different approach by fully automating treatment pathways. It delivers diagnosis, treatment, and discharge without human oversight. This makes it one of the most autonomous healthcare systems in the sector.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company is now expanding into broader clinical domains. Its AI systems are being trained on new condition areas. These include orthopaedic and women’s health pathways.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investor Albion VC said the company has proven real world impact. It highlighted strong NHS results and regulatory trust. The firm believes the opportunity extends beyond physiotherapy alone.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Flok now faces the challenge of scaling safely across new conditions. Maintaining clinical outcomes and regulatory approval remains critical. The company’s next stage will test whether autonomous care can expand further.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/flok-health-raises-12-5m-ai-healthcare/" data-wpel-link="internal">Flok Health Raises $12.5M to Scale AI Operated Healthcare Platform</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
