					<description><![CDATA[<p>Building a Connected Operating System for Ranchers 701x has raised more than $10 million in an oversubscribed Series B funding round. The Fargo-based agricultural technology company was backed entirely by</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/701x-raises-10m-series-b-cattle-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">701x Raises $10M+ Series B to Expand Cattle Tech Ecosystem</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Building a Connected Operating System for Ranchers</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">701x has raised more than $10 million in an oversubscribed Series B funding round. The Fargo-based agricultural technology company was backed entirely by ranchers and local investors. No venture capital or institutional investors took part in the round. The company continues to expand its cattle-focused technology ecosystem across global markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding comes as 701x reaches early profitability and prepares for international expansion. The company has built an integrated platform for beef cattle producers. Its tools combine GPS tracking, herd management software, and DNA solutions. The new capital will support product development and operational scaling.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">701x was founded by CEO Kevin Biffert to modernise cattle ranching operations. The company develops an integrated ecosystem for beef producers. Its platform connects software, hardware, and genetic tools into a single system. This allows ranchers to manage herds more efficiently across large and remote land areas.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">At the centre of the platform is the xTpro smart ear tag. The device uses GPS and satellite connectivity to track cattle in real time. It monitors key events such as fence breaches, health changes, </span><a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/breeding-cycle" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">breeding cycles</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">, and calving activity. It also detects issues in bull fertility and herd behaviour.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The system is designed for environments with limited or no cellular coverage. It transmits data via satellite every 15 minutes. This allows ranchers to monitor livestock across thousands of acres. It replaces manual herd checks that are time-consuming and inconsistent.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">701x combines this hardware with a digital software platform. The system includes ranch management tools and breed association software. It also integrates DNA testing and genetic tracking solutions. Together, these components form a unified cattle management ecosystem.</span></p>
<h2><b>Community Funding and Early Profitability</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The Series B round was fully funded by ranchers and local investors. Investors came primarily from North Dakota, Minnesota, and surrounding regions. The company deliberately avoided venture capital participation. This structure reflects its focus on customer-driven growth.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">701x has also reached profitability, achieving its first profitable month recently. The company continues to invest heavily in research and development. It is also improving its acquired breed registry software and developing new feedlot management tools. Growth is being driven without reliance on external institutional capital.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO Kevin Biffert said the funding reflects strong community support. He highlighted that many investors are also customers of the platform. This creates a feedback loop between product usage and capital formation. It also strengthens adoption across ranching communities.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has reduced production costs through automation and robotics. Manufacturing improvements have lowered assembly costs for its xTpro device by 75 percent. This allows 701x to scale production while maintaining cost efficiency. The strategy is rooted in Biffert’s background in industrial automation.</span></p>
<h2><b>Expanding Across Global Livestock Markets<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202309" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202309" class="size-full wp-image-202309" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-with_gIcPv2eUUfa3gXYDDb4tjw_yS-4wNYkQ0O_4jEnKJv_2g.png" alt="Connected livestock intelligence system enabling real-time herd monitoring and global ranch management." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202309" class="wp-caption-text">701x expands globally with smart cattle tracking and integrated livestock management technology. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">701x is now preparing for international expansion. The company already operates in Canada. It plans to enter Australia, New Zealand, Mexico, the United Kingdom, and Brazil before the end of the year. These regions represent large cattle-producing markets with similar operational challenges.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform is designed to address two major industry problems. These are livestock fertility management and animal health monitoring. A single missed breeding cycle or illness can result in significant financial losses. 701x aims to reduce these risks through automated detection systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s GPS ear tag technology is central to its expansion strategy. It enables real-time monitoring of cattle across remote environments. This capability is particularly important in large-scale ranching operations. It allows producers to act quickly on health or breeding alerts.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">701x also continues to expand its software ecosystem. The company acquired DigitalBeef to strengthen its breed association capabilities. This added pedigree tracking and performance data tools to its platform. It also helps consolidate fragmented data systems used in livestock management.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/bibliu-raises-55m-campus-store-expansion/" data-wpel-link="internal">BibliU Raises $55M to Scale Integrated Campus Store Platform</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Market Position and Industry Transformation</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">701x operates in the growing agricultural technology sector. The company is focused specifically on beef cattle producers. Its integrated model combines hardware, software, and genetic data into one platform. This approach differentiates it from single-function agtech tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CEO Kevin Biffert’s background in automation has influenced the company’s strategy. His previous experience in manufacturing helped reduce production costs significantly. This gives 701x control over its hardware supply chain. It also improves long-term scalability and margin structure.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s model reflects a broader shift in agricultural technology. Ranchers are increasingly adopting digital tools to manage livestock. However, many existing solutions remain fragmented. 701x aims to unify these systems into a single operating platform.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding structure also highlights a unique market approach. By relying on customer-investors, the company aligns product development with user needs. This reduces dependence on traditional venture capital cycles. It also strengthens long-term product adoption within the ranching community.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">701x continues to scale its operations across North America and beyond. The company is building a connected infrastructure for cattle management. Its focus remains on improving efficiency, reducing losses, and digitising ranch operations. The latest funding round supports its transition into global markets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/701x-raises-10m-series-b-cattle-tech/" data-wpel-link="internal">701x Raises $10M+ Series B to Expand Cattle Tech Ecosystem</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
