					<description><![CDATA[<p>Building an AI-Driven Data Security Platform Cyera has raised $300 million in new funding, pushing its valuation to $12 billion. The AI data security company continues rapid expansion in the</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cyera-raises-300m-series-funding-12b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cyera Raises $300M Series Funding at $12B Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Building an AI-Driven Data Security Platform</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cyera has raised $300 million in new funding, pushing its valuation to $12 billion. The AI data security company continues rapid expansion in the enterprise cybersecurity market. The round reflects strong investor confidence in data protection infrastructure for AI systems. It also marks a significant increase in the company’s valuation trajectory.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding comes as Cyera expands its platform capabilities and acquisition strategy. The company focuses on helping organisations discover and secure sensitive data across cloud environments. Its tools reduce data blind spots and improve overall security visibility. Investors support its ambition to become a foundational layer in enterprise AI security systems.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cyera, founded in 2021 by CEO Yotam Segev and CTO Tamar Bar-Ilan, operates an AI-powered platform. It enables companies to visualise where data is stored and how it is used. It also identifies and categorises </span><a href="https://www.hyperbots.com/glossary/data-risk" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">data risk</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> across cloud and SaaS applications. This allows organisations to enforce stronger access controls and security policies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The platform addresses a growing challenge in enterprise IT environments. Large volumes of unstructured data are created daily and become difficult to track. Cyera aims to eliminate visibility gaps through automated discovery and classification tools. This improves control and reduces security risks across organisations.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Operating within data security posture management, Cyera benefits from rising AI adoption across industries. Enterprises increasingly require stronger protections for data used in AI systems. Cyera positions itself as a critical enabling layer in this ecosystem.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company reportedly generates over $150 million in annual recurring revenue from global enterprise clients. Strong growth indicates low adoption barriers and rising demand. Enterprises seek solutions that balance AI-driven innovation with effective risk management and data security.</span></p>
<h2><b>$300M Funding Round Backed by Major Investors</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The $300 million round was led by Evolution Equity Partners. The firm is known for its focus on cybersecurity investments. Other participants include Georgian, Greenoaks, Lightspeed Venture Partners, Sequoia Capital, Sapphire Ventures, Redpoint Ventures, Cyberstarts, Coatue, Accel, and Spark Capital.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding increases Cyera’s total capital raised to more than $2 billion. It also places the company among the most highly valued cybersecurity startups globally. The valuation rise reflects growing demand for AI-native security platforms.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cyera has raised capital at a fast pace over the past two years. It was valued at $6 billion late last year. That figure rose to $9 billion in January 2026. The latest round now places it at $12 billion, more than doubling in under a year.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors are betting on Cyera’s expansion strategy. The company has already completed several acquisitions. These include Genie Security, Ryft, Trail Security, Otterize, and Shape AI. Each acquisition strengthens its capabilities in data governance and security automation.</span></p>
<h2><b>Expansion Strategy Through Acquisitions and AI Growth<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_202289" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202289" class="size-full wp-image-202289" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/create-a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-elem_yyyfBOuOUEiEMQje8CruMQ_aEWPvbZHSR-bwLNgScJUBg_cover.png" alt="Unified data security platform with AI-driven protection and cloud automation systems." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-202289" class="wp-caption-text">Cyera is building a unified platform to secure enterprise data in an AI-driven world. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cyera is pursuing an aggressive growth and acquisition strategy. The company aims to consolidate tools across the data security market. It wants to offer a unified platform for discovery, classification, and protection.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Recent acquisitions highlight this strategy. Ryft added AI-ready data infrastructure capabilities. Genie Security strengthened automation in cloud environments. Earlier deals like Trail Security expanded its enterprise security coverage.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chief Executive Yotam Segev has said the company aims to become a category leader in data security. He has compared its ambition to major cybersecurity platforms in adjacent markets. The goal is to build a unified system for enterprise data protection at scale.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s growth is closely tied to AI adoption. Enterprises are increasingly feeding sensitive data into AI systems. This creates new risks around exposure and compliance. Cyera’s platform is designed to address these risks directly.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The firm now competes in a rapidly expanding global cybersecurity landscape. Demand is rising as organisations struggle with data sprawl across cloud systems. This environment has created a strong investor appetite for platforms like Cyera.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/impulse-space-raises-500m-series-d-orbital-mobility/" data-wpel-link="internal">Impulse Space Raises $500M Series D to Build Orbital Mobility Infrastructure</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Market Position and Future Growth Pressure</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cyera’s latest valuation places it among the top privately held Israeli tech companies. It sits just behind data infrastructure firm Vast Data and ahead of DriveNets. The company has quickly become a major player in the global cybersecurity market.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">However, rapid valuation growth brings pressure to deliver. Cyera must continue scaling revenue to match investor expectations. It must also integrate its recent acquisitions successfully. Execution will be critical at this stage of expansion.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has raised funding multiple times in a short period. This includes $400 million earlier in 2026 and $540 million in the previous year. Each round has significantly increased its valuation. It shows investor conviction in the long-term market space for it.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Cyera continues to develop and advance the capabilities of its platform over cloud environments with a strategy aimed at providing enterprise data visibility and lowering the security alert volume and increasing security risk detection precision.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The overall data security market is growing, and AI deployment is creating demand for secure data infrastructure that places Cyera at the forefront with a combination of platform expansion and acquisitions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Investors consider Cyera to be a long-term category leader as the company&#8217;s rapid rise and strong financing demonstrate belief in its market opportunity. Moving forward it must balance scaling with maintaining high product performance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/cyera-raises-300m-series-funding-12b-valuation/" data-wpel-link="internal">Cyera Raises $300M Series Funding at $12B Valuation</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
